Title: Series: Prints in Imitation of Drawings
Description: St Anthony pursued by demons: Anthony standing in the right foreground in front of pillars, looking back towards a group of demons who stand around the corner of the pillars on the left and look towards him; after Cambiaso. 1736 Etching with woodcut from thre blocks in brown ink
Curator's comments: For another impression, see 1936,1116.2126.15. For the series, see comment in 1936,1116.2126.1.
Bibliographic references: Hake 1922 / Pond & Knapton's Imitations of Drawing (3)
Associated names: Representation of: St Antony of Egypt
Acquisition notes: There was no registration number on this object, hence the new U number was given when catalogued.
